==English==
{{wikipedia}}
[[Category:Mammals]]

===Etymology===
Leo + pard. In mediaevel times it was thought that a leopard was a cross between a lion [[leo]] and a [[pard]] or black panther.

===Noun===
'''leopard''' (''plural'' '''[[leopards]]''')
# A large wild [[cat]] with a spotted coat, ''Panthera pardus'', indigenous to Africa and Asia.

====Related Terms====
*[[leopard's head]]
*[[leopard cannot change its spots]]

